Description
Jane Eyre is a 1983 British television serial dramatisation of Charlotte Bronte's romantic novel. It was produced by BBC and directed by Julian Amyes. The serial stars Zelah Clarke as the title character, and Timothy Dalton as Edward Rochester. Deene Park, located near Corby, Northamptonshire was used as the setting of Rochester's Thornfield Hall.
